On International Women's Day, the article highlights the importance of women in shaping and strengthening communities, families, governments, and businesses. It acknowledges the progress made in the fight for equality and justice through initiatives promoting women's economic empowerment. The Women's Global Development and Prosperity (W-GDP) Initiative is mentioned as a historic initiative aimed at helping 50 million women in developing countries participate in their local economies by 2025. The article also mentions the administration's efforts to support women in the United States through tax relief and job creation. It emphasizes that when women are economically empowered, it leads to economic growth and global stability. The commitment to equality and opportunity for all women is reaffirmed.